text.tspan: Cairo is chaos at its most magnificent, infuriating and
beautiful. From above, the distorted roar of the
muezzinsâ€™ call to prayer echoes out from duelling
minarets. Below, car horns bellow tuneless
grandeur while donkey carts rattle down dusty lanes
lined with colossal Fatimid and Mamluk monuments.
